---
title: Louisiana-Style Tilapia with Potato Wedges, Red Cabbage Slaw & Spicy Remoulade
description: Cue the brass band, because your taste buds are about to take a trip to the Big Easy! We’re talking ultra-crunchy, spiced tilapia fillets with sides of cabbage-carrot slaw and crispy potato wedges. It’s all finished with a drizzle of one of our all-time favorite condiments: zingy, creamy remoulade. Now if only this came with beignets for dessert...
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/620c1ee55db7411a8f13491e-63a699f5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/louisiana-style-tilapia-620c1ee55db7411a8f13491e-6a631f57.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/louisiana-style-tilapia-620c1ee55db7411a8f13491e
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1380 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; finely chop whites until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Finely chop @chili pepper{1}. Trim, peel, and grate @carrot{3%ounce} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}; place in a #medium bowl{}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, chopped scallion whites, one packet @sour cream{4%tablespoon} (two packets for 4 servings), 1 tsp @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of chili to taste. (You'll use the rest of the sour cream and vinegar later.) Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

To bowl with carrot, add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, two packets sour cream (four packets for 4 servings), remaining vinegar, 2 TBSP scallion greens (4 TBSP for 4), and @sugar{1.5%teaspoon} (3 tsp for 4). (You'll use the rest of the sour cream in the next step.) Season with a big pinch of salt and pepper; toss to combine.

Halve @tilapia{11%ounce} fillets lengthwise (you'll have a larger piece and a smaller piece). Pat dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1}, remaining sour cream, and 1 TBSP @water{} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

On a #plate{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} and @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}.

Dip each fillet into sour cream mixture, then press into panko mixture, coating all over.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko mixture sizzles when added to pan, add tilapia and cook until crust is golden and fish is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (The smaller pieces will cook faster). (For 4 servings, fry fish in batches.) Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

Divide potatoes, slaw, and tilapia between plates. Serve with remoulade. Garnish with any remaining scallion greens.